;; -*- mode: outline; -*-

Emacs Cheat Sheet

* Motion
M-< | M->	 : go to beginning / end of buffer
M-{ 	| M-}	 : go to beginning / end of paragraph

* Marking
C-SPC		: set mark here
C-x C-x		: exchange point and mark

* Bookmarks
C-x r m		: set bookmark
C-x r b		: jump to bookmark

* Registers
C-x r <spc> p : save point to register "p"
C-x r j p	       : jump to point stored in register "p"
C-x r s p	       : copy region to register "p"
C-x r i p	       : insert from point "p"
M-x view-register

* Outline mode
To enable, set first line to be:  ;; -*- mode: outline; -*-
C-c C-d	       : hide all under this heading
C-c C-s 	       : show all under this heading
C-c C-n 	       : move point to next heading
C-c C-p 	       : move point to previous heading
C-c C-t 	       : hide all headings
C-c C-a 	       : show all headings

* Windows
C-x o		: switch to other window
C-x 0		: delete this window
C-x 1		: delete all other windows
C-x 2		: split window above and below point
C-x 3		: split widow side-by-side
C-x 4 f	  	: find file in other window
C-x 4 d		: run dired in other window

* Abbreviations
M-x define-global-abbrev

* Formatting
C-o			: insert newline after point
C-x C-o		: delete blank lines around point
M-q		  	: fill paragraph
C-M-\		: indent region (mode dependent)

* Misc
C-x 4 a		: new changelog entry
C-x a l	        : add local abbrv for word before point
C-x a g		: add global abbrev for word before point
M-x ispell region | buffer  : ispell region / buffer
